===Noun===
#A low-ranking soldier who merely carries a pike.
#A. lower class (often unemployed) lowlife; specifically Irish travellers or gypsies, but now sometimes used for any socially undesirable elements. Encompasses connotations of benefit fraud, theft, illegitimate children and run-down council estates. Derived from the old English word 'pike', meaning to depart or travel. Other theories include pikey being a derivation of 'turnpike sailor'.